Project Title:
OptiCrop - Intelligent Crop Recommendation System

Module Name:
Logistic Regression Model Building

Objective:
The objective of this module is to build a machine learning model that predicts the most suitable crop based on soil nutrients and environmental conditions.

Algorithm Used:
Logistic Regression

Description:
Logistic Regression is a supervised machine learning algorithm used for classification problems. In this project, the algorithm is trained using agricultural data to recommend suitable crops for cultivation.

Input Features:
1. Nitrogen (N)
2. Phosphorus (P)
3. Potassium (K)
4. Temperature
5. Humidity
6. pH Value
7. Rainfall
8. Cluster

Target Variable:
Crop Label

Dataset:
Clustered_Dataset.csv

Methodology:

Step 1:
Load the clustered dataset using Pandas.

Step 2:
Separate input features (X) and target variable (y).

Step 3:
Split the dataset into training and testing datasets using Train-Test Split.

Step 4:
Create a Logistic Regression model.

Step 5:
Train the model using training data.

Step 6:
Save the trained model as logistic_model.pkl.

Tools and Technologies:
• Python
• Pandas
• NumPy
• Scikit-Learn
• Jupyter Notebook

Output:
• Trained Logistic Regression Model
• logistic_model.pkl file

Advantages:
• Simple and efficient classification algorithm.
• Fast training and prediction.
• Easy to implement.
• Suitable for crop recommendation systems.

Conclusion:
The Logistic Regression model was successfully trained using the clustered agricultural dataset. The trained model can be used to predict suitable crops based on soil and environmental parameters.
